==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[wargeld]], from {{ang}} [[ƿergeld]], compound of [[ƿer]], ''man'' + [[geld]], ''payment''.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[weregeld]]
*[[weregild]]
*[[wergild]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{archaic}}: In Anglo-Saxon and Germanic law, a reparational payment usually demanded of a person guilty of homicide or other serious crimes.

